id: pm-topu
title: "GH-551: dependency seeds accept global source_kind and preserve cross-workspace IDs"
description: Align the documented dependency seed contract with runtime behavior and make cross-workspace relationship IDs explicit and lossless instead of silently applying the local id_prefix.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: data-integrity,gh-551,relationships
created_at: "2026-07-14T10:18:53.997Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T10:14:19.230Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T10:14:18.200Z"
author: codex-gpt5
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "The CLI either accepts and preserves documented source_kind for external dependencies or removes it with a safe replacement; external IDs are never silently rewritten; help, SDK contracts, validation, and integration tests agree."
parent: pm-96h7
risk: medium
confidence: 75
resolution: Added public dependency provenance primitives and source_kind-aware create/update/graph behavior for external IDs.
expected_result: Cross-workspace dependency IDs remain lossless and graph validation distinguishes external targets from dangling local references.
actual_result: "Global IDs round-trip through create, graph, update removal, and get with missing_nodes equal to zero."
