comments[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:18:53.997Z",codex-gpt5,"Duplicate check 2026-07-14: pm search GH-551 --status all returned no item. This is related to the active relationship registry lineage pm-ju83 but is not implemented in the current in-memory graph primitive bundle. Source: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/551"
  "2026-07-21T07:33:03.401Z",codex-root-20260721,"Evidence: create and update now share public normalizeDependencySeedId semantics; source_kind=global preserves foreign IDs, removes with the same selector, materializes external graph nodes, and yields missing_nodes=0 instead of a dangling local reference."
  "2026-07-21T07:54:56.539Z",codex-root-20260721,"Final verification: public provenance helpers and CLI round-trip suites pass directly from source; repo-wide coverage remains exactly 100/100/100/100 with no ignored external-identity branches."
  "2026-07-21T08:12:06.270Z",codex-root-20260721,"Greptile remediation: graph assembly now gives real local and missing-local identities precedence over external placeholders, preventing duplicate node IDs and conflicting detail statuses when the same case-insensitive target is referenced with mixed provenance. Added a direct mixed-provenance regression."
  "2026-07-21T08:16:40.217Z",codex-root-20260721,"Final review-head proof: the mixed-provenance duplicate-node regression passes within the full 6052-test suite at exact 100% coverage."
  "2026-07-21T09:10:30.372Z",codex-root-20260721,"Hosted review remediation: external source kinds are canonicalized case-insensitively on create, add, persistence, dedupe, and removal; graph assembly now preserves both local and external identities with deterministic collision-free node IDs. The CLI acceptance test covers mixed-case add/dedupe/remove and the SDK test covers local/missing/external collisions."
  "2026-07-21T09:15:15.946Z",codex-root-20260721,"Exact remediation-head proof: all 332 test files and 6053 tests pass; coverage is 100% statements (40688/40688), branches (28623/28623), functions (8264/8264), and lines (39582/39582)."
  "2026-07-21T10:13:37.936Z",codex-root-20260721,"Hosted CodeRabbit remediation: canonical title now describes the delivered behavior so pm-changelog produces an affirmative release entry instead of defect wording."
